HEADWORD: Elaidic
<hw>E`la*id"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧la⟦ium⟧dique</ets>. See <er>Elaine</er>.]</ety>
<def>Relating to oleic acid, or elaine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Elaidic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a fatty
acid isomeric with oleic acid, and obtained from it by the action of
nitrous acid.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elaidin</ent>⟦br⟧
